	(text "- The CANH and CANL lines are connected to the 3 pin TD connector. As of date the pinout is TBD,\n   might be swapped.\n- The CAN Address Dip Switch should control the least significant 3 bits of the board's CAN ID.\n   This will allow upto 8 CAN ID variations, as per the reqs.\n- The GPIOs are exposed, and thus have 4 channel unidirectional TVS diode arrays. RWM voltage\n   is 3.6V.\n- Since the SWD pins are exposed, there's the same 3.6v RWM diodes. But if the stlink programmer\n   operates at 5V (gpios are 5V tolerant), will need to unsolder this IC.\n- VBUS will NOT power the STM; external 12V is always required. Ground is shared.\n- The USB DP DM filter is MODIFIED from the custom library symbol. Restore if modified.\n- NRST is active low with internal weak pullup."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 163.83 25.654 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "ac7928e1-a4d6-455a-8d7c-bf31fd808cd1")
	)
